Victoria McKennon is just one class short of the credits she needs to graduate from Plano Senior High School in Texas . 
  She is desperate to take part in the graduation ceremony in June . 
  The 17-year-old suffers from cystic fibrosis and has had to miss dozens of lessons due to her life-threatening condition . 
  School officials refused to let her take part and said she could graduate in the summer but not with her friends . 
  Family has filed a civil rights complaint with the Department of Education . 
 